 of García Márquez's Colombia. Lorna Robinson holds a PhD in Classics from University College London. She is the author of Cave Canem: A Miscellany of Latin Words and Phrases and the essay 'The Golden Age in Metamorphoses' and 'One Hundred Years of Solitude' in A Companion to Magical Realism (Tamesis, 2005).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMagic in literature. 0aPolitics in literature. 4aHispanic Studies. 4aModern Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Caribbean & Latin American.2bisacsh  aCulture.  aGabriel García Márquez.  aLiterary Realities.  aMagical Realism.  aMetamorphoses.  aOvid.  aPolitics.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178204066840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782040668423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782040668/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles